bio.experienceSummary: I have over 10 years of experience working in childcare with children of all ages. I enjoy doing crafts and outdoor activities! I look forward to hearing from you and answering any questions you may have for me!

bio.experienceSummary: I have over 25 years of experience with newborns, infant, toddlers, twins and school-aged children. I describe myself as a loving, responsible and caring person. I like walking to parks, performing daily activities with other children and parents will always be well informed before I make any decisions, so they can always count on me when they need me. I have my First Aid and CPR certification and I am also a certified newborn care specialist. I drive very carefully and I have never had an accident while driving because a child's safety is very important to me. I truly love what I do and I am excited to start a new journey with a new family.

description.originalText: Any family with young children would be so lucky to have Yolanda! She's a career nanny with 20+ years of experience that came highly recommended to us by all of her previous families. She's very caring, loving and energetic and made my transition back to work so much easier. My son would get so excited when she walked through the door in the morning. Yolanda kept my son very active, organized playdates, did laundry, prepared nutritious meals, and kept the house very tidy. She's a newborn care specialist, so is very knowledgeable on milestones. She speaks both Spanish and English, has her own car/transportation, and is CPR and First Aid certified.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello everyone!

I have experience with kids on all ages so i'm able to provide a safe and rich environment and understand their needs depending on the stage they are so you won't have to worry about them while i'm on guard!

I consider myself a very positive, reliable, fun, creative and very patient person who loves being around little ones, plus I follow the idea of gentle parenting style.

Communication is a key for me and i'll keep you posted on how the shift is going and can do extra chores that are need it upon request.

description.originalText: Laura was absolutely fantastic taking care of our 18month old boy. She came right in, listening to everything we had to share about his schedule, and had him laughing and in her arms within minutes. She fed him, played around the house, and bathed him before putting him down for bed. She kept us updated while we were out with cute pictures of him. We would definitely recommend her for any family looking for someone both caring and super reliable.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, I'm a former teacher and mom of 4 children who are now ages 19-25. I'm Math teacher by education and training. I speak both English and Russian. 
I'm mature, caring, patient, attentive, engaging, experienced in infant/ child care and education. I'm reliable and punctual. I've been assisting families with infants and young children in Bayonne, Jersey City, Hoboken, Weehawken, NYC. I love to read to the children, engage them in fun and educational activities. I will create safe environment for your child. I also enjoy taking kids to the park/ playground ( weather/ CDC guidelines permit).
I'm up to date with Flu, Pneumonia, TDaP vaccinations.
I'm fully vaccinated and boosted.
By all means I welcome background check.

description.originalText:
Whatever I write here will not do Svetlana justice. She was flexible and endlessly kind and she helped us make our weekend trip a resounding success. She walked in and my nephew was almost immediately at ease. He had such a good time with Svetlana singing and drawing together. She certainly left an impression as he was asking about her after we'd left town. 

Anyway, I can't really say enough good things. Thank you Svetlana for taking care of our little guy.

bio.experienceSummary: I've been a childcare provider for 12 years because I'm passionate about nurturing children's development. I'm patient, creative, and formal. I keep parents informed about their child's day and address any issues that arise through written daily reports, verbal communication, and regular updates. While I prefer a relaxed approach, I'm comfortable enforcing household rules when necessary. I enjoy a variety of games with children, from educational to technology-based. I'm comfortable caring for up to four children, and I have experience with children of all ages. My graduate degree and Spanish fluency further enhance my ability to provide a well-rounded and nurturing environment for the children in my care.

I am a 39-year-old mother of one wonderful 14-year-old girl now a 9th grader and she is the love of my life! I have over 13+ years of experience as a nanny. I can provide excellent verifiable reference available. I am seeking work ideally in Brooklyn and Staten Island, Manhattan. I am a hands on individual who enjoys arts and crafts, singing, reading and above all playing with children. I take care of all the light housekeeping duties pertaining to the children as well. I can run any errands you might need done, groceries, laundry and clean up the nursery/room. I have several reliable transportation options. Most importantly I will treat and care for your children as if they were my own. Their safety and well being is of utmost importance to me. CPR and first aide certified. I enjoy the outdoors and recreation.

description.originalText: We had a trial run with Erika and she was excellent. The moment she stepped in, she was professional and definitely showed a high standard of care.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Madeline, I am 26 years old and am currently a full-time student during the day and have been working with children ranging from 6 months through 12 years old, as well as adults with physical disabilities. I love board games, cooking, and gardening!

My name is Khayanna, many call me Paris. From play time to homework time, it's always a good time! I emphasize learning through play. I graduated from MSU, with a B. A. in Child Advocacy&Policy, I enjoyed being so involved in school activities&was dancer at the school. I like to spread my positive energy&smile! I was a Teacher Assistant then quickly Lead Teacher in a child care center. Swiftly arises to the Administrative Assistant and now the Assistant Director within the same company. I am also a Behavioral Assistant/Tutor/Mentor aside with a different agency. I hope I can be a great fit with your family & spread joy your way

description.originalText: Khayanna is the best, she’s been watching our little girl on weekends and date nights. She’s  reliable and has been super helpful especially when we’re looking for care last minute. Khayanna is sweet personality and appreciative that she takes the time to play with our daughter.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello my name is Svetlana. I am a mother of two children. I am honest, kind, caring, reliable, responsible and positive person and have enjoyed working with children in past. I be happy to help around the house, prepare and organize meal times and snacks for children.

Hello! I'm Nicole and I'm a professional child care provider. I'm first aid, CPR and EMT certified. I have years of experience caring for newborns, toddlers and primary school children. I'm available for full-time, live out, occasional, and part-time nanny roles.

I'm passionate about providing a safe and nurturing environment that helps children reach their full potential. I'm highly experienced with routine creation and planning age appropriate activities that will engage and stimulate the children. 

If you're looking for a professional child care provider for your newborn, toddler, or primary school child, I'd love to hear from you. Please feel free to message me if you're interested!
